      • setExternal

        public void setExternal(boolean external)
        Description copied from class: VariableDeclaration
        Set whether or not the variable is external. A variable is external if it is referenced from a language outside of Nova. For example, a variable from the C language. Furthermore, a variable is external if it begins with an externally imported C file's name.

        For example: 
         import "externalFile.h";
 
 ...
 
 public static void main(String args[])
 {
        // This is the external variable declaration.
        externalFile.externalType varName;
        
        // This is the external variable assignment.
        varName = externalFile.variableInstance;
 }
        In this example, 'externalFile' is the C header file that is imported. 'variableInstance' is the name of a variable that is contained within the imported header file.
        Overrides:
        setExternal in class VariableDeclaration
        Parameters:
        external - Whether or not the variable will be external.
        See Also:
        VariableDeclaration.setExternal(boolean)

      • getParameterList

        public ParameterList<Value> getParameterList()
        The the ParameterList that represents the parameters of the method.
        For example:
         public void methodName(int age, String name);
        In the previous statement, the data within the parenthesis are the parameters of the method. The ParameterList returned by this method would contain a node for each of the parameter specified, in the correct order from left to right.
        Specified by:
        getParameterList in interface CallableMethod
        Returns:
        The ParameterList that represents the parameters of the method.

      • getParameter

        public Value getParameter(int parameterIndex)
        Get the Parameter that the given index represents. The parameters are ordered from left to right, 0 being the first.

        For example: 
         public void run(int a, int b, int c)
 {
        ...
 }
        If you were to call getParameter(2) on the method above, you would receive the c Parameter.
        Parameters:
        parameterIndex - The index parameter to get.
        Returns:
        The Parameter at the given index.

      • generateCSourcePrototype

        public java.lang.StringBuilder generateCSourcePrototype(java.lang.StringBuilder builder)
        Generate the C prototype for the method header.

        For example: 
         public void test()
 {
        ...
 }
        will output as "static void test();"

        In essence, this method is just generateCSourceSignature(StringBuilder) with a semi-colon attached to the end.
        Parameters:
        builder - The StringBuilder to append the data to.
        Returns:
        The C prototype for the method header.
